<text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="PaLTM3.6.2">
<l>iṭavaṇa raiyiṭat tōḷoṭu cāyt</l>
<l rend="indent">tirukaikū ṭappuru vannerin tēṟa</l>
<l>kuṭavayi ṟupaṭa vāykaṭai kūṭak</l>
<l rend="indent">kōvintaṉ kuḻalko ṭūtiṉa pōtu</l>
<l>maṭamayil kaḷoṭu māṉpiṇai pōlē</l>
<l rend="indent">maṅkaimār kaḷmalark kūntala viḻa</l>
<l>vuṭaine kiḻavōr kaiyāltukil paṟṟi</l>
<l rend="indent">yolkiyō ṭarikkaṇō ṭaniṉṟa ṉarē.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>When Govinda played [his] flute with the corner of [his] mouth,</l>
<l rend="indent">such that [his cheek] appeared [like] a round belly,</l>
<l rend="indent">the left side of [his] jaw bent to [his] left shoulder,</l>
<l rend="indent">[his] two hands united [with his flute],</l>
<l rend="indent">and [his] eyebrows arched up,</l>
<l>the maidens,</l>
<l rend="indent">–like female deer and simple peacocks–</l>
<l>as [their] blossomed tresses become loose,</l>
<l rend="indent">[and] garments slip off,</l>
<l rend="indent">grasping at [their] saris with one hand, trembling,</l>
<l>stood [still] while [their] line streaked eyes ran [after him].</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
</text>
